# Change Log

All notable changes to brdkSTR  will be documented in this file.
brdkSTR  adheres to [Semantic Versioning](http://semver.org/).

## [Unreleased]
- encode / decode
	- base 32
	- base 64

## [1.12.0] - 2022-06-14
### Added
- brdkStrDTStructureToA() - Added format input to output date and time in various formats

## [1.11.0] - 2022-06-11
### Added
- brdkStrAToReal() - Converts a string to a REAL type. NB. Implementation not equal to atof(). 
- brdkStrRealToA() - Converts a REAL into a STRING type. NB. Implementation not equal to ftoa().

## [1.10.1] - 2022-06-10
### Fixed
- brdkStrSearch() - Fix when search string was equal to source string

## [1.10.0] - 2022-06-04
### Added
- brdkStrUdintLen() - Returns the number of characters the UDINT value would fill in a STRING.
- brdkStrDintLen() - Returns the number of characters the DINT value would fill in a STRING.

## [1.9.0] - 2022-06-03
### Added
- brdkStrAppendDintToA() - Appends an DINT to the end of a string.

## [1.8.0] - 2021-03-18
### Added
- brdkStrNAToUdint() - Converts a string to an UDINT type for amount of characters. If the function encounters a null character in the source string, if will stop.
- brdkStrNAToDint() - Converts a string to an DINT type for amount of characters. If the function encounters a null character in the source string, if will stop.
- brdkStrNIsDigit() - Returns false or true depending of the amount characters are digits.
- brdkStrNIsAlphabet() - Returns false or true depending of the amount of characters are present in the alphabet.
- brdkStrDTStructureToA() - Converts a DTStructure into a STRING type in format yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss.ms.
- brdkStrAToDTStructure() - Converts a STRING of format yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss.ms into a DTStructure.

- ASCII characters constants. 

## [1.7.0] - 2020-12-20
### Added
- brdkStrSubDintSearch() - Returns a DINT based on a search.
- brdkStrSubStrSearch() - Returns a part of a string based on a search.
- brdkStrMemClear() - Fills amount of 0 to destination.

## [1.6.0] - 2020-11-11
### Added
- brdkStrSplit() - Splits a string into an array by a delimiter.
- brdkStrJoin() - Joins elements from a string array into a string with a delimiter.
- brdkStrIsAlphabet() - Returns false or true depending of all characters are present in the alphabet. a..z = true.
- brdkStrIsDigit() - Returns false or true depending of all characters are digits. 0..9 = true.
- brdkStrWord() - Returns a word in a string given by a number and a delimiter.

## [1.5.0] - 2020-03-01
### Added
- brdkStrFillUp() - Fills a string with x amount of chars until max length is reached.

## [1.4.0] - 2019-04-10
### Added
- brdkStrIsEmpty() - Returns false or true depending of characters are present in the first position of the string.

## [1.3.1] - 2017-01-12
### Fixed
- brdkStrMemMove() - Bug in mem move block where the 1 bytes after amount was set to 0.

## [1.3.0] - 2016-08-02
- brdkCrc32() - Calculates a CRC32 checksum based on the input string.

## [1.2.0] - 2016-07-25
### Added
- brdkStrMemCpy() -  Copies amount of character(s) from source to destination. NO overlapping buffer support.
- brdkStrMemMove() - Moves amount of character(s) from source to destination. Supports overlaying buffer.
- brdkStrMove() - Moves a string to another string. Supports overlapping buffers.
- brdkStrMemCmp() - Compares two memory areas.
- brdkStrMemSet() - Fills amount of character(s) to destination.
- brdkStrCmp() - Compares two strings.
- brdkStrNCpy() - Copies a string to another string. If the function encounters a null character in the source string, the function will add null characters to the destination string until amount character(s) have been written. 
- brdkStrDintToA() - Converts a DINT into a STRING type.
- brdkStrAToDint() - Converts a string to a DINT type.

### Changed
- brdkStrCpy() - no longer supports an overlapping buffer. Use brdkStrMove() for this instead.
- now support brdkGenHelp() script.

## [1.1.0] - 2016-01-11
### Added
- See help for complete function addition list

## [1.0.0] - 2015-12-17
### Added
- All functions
- Help files
